  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n1 emoji = 2 chars, so in case when text + emoji > limit for field (i.e. 4096 for chat input, 600 for status), value is erased\r\nReproducible on different text inputs on IOS (message input, group chat invite field, status input etc)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\ncan't type emoji, as it 2 chars\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nwhen typing emoji, value is erased\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/146220608-32869769-7fa8-4cf0-8b6a-97ef8d4bf12b.mp4\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Open Status\r\n2) Open status tab > +\r\n3) Paste text with 599 chars\r\n4) Type emoji\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: 1.18 \r\n- Operating System:  iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
